{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1627,"text":"Do you ever think about how important\nthe oceans are in our daily lives?"},{"time":7830,"text":"The oceans cover two-thirds of our planet."},{"time":11190,"text":"They provide half the oxygen we breathe."},{"time":14036,"text":"They moderate our climate."},{"time":16055,"text":"And they provide jobs\nand medicine and food"},{"time":20181,"text":"including 20 percent of protein\nto feed the entire world population."},{"time":26331,"text":"People used to think\nthat the oceans were so vast"},{"time":28872,"text":"that they wouldn't be affected\nby human activities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":32205,"text":"Well today I'm going to tell you\nabout a serious reality"},{"time":35516,"text":"that is changing our oceans\ncalled ocean acidification,"},{"time":40363,"text":"or the evil twin of climate change."},{"time":43900,"text":"Did you know that the oceans have absorbed\n25 percent of all of the carbon dioxide"},{"time":49347,"text":"that we have emitted to the atmosphere?"},{"time":51970,"text":"Now this is just another great service\nprovided by the oceans"},{"time":55633,"text":"since carbon dioxide\nis one of the greenhouse gases"},{"time":58527,"text":"that's causing climate change."},{"time":61310,"text":"But as we keep pumping\nmore and more and more"},{"time":65372,"text":"carbon dioxide into the atmosphere"},{"time":68030,"text":"more is dissolving into the oceans."},{"time":70803,"text":"And this is what's changing\nour ocean chemistry."},{"time":75350,"text":"When carbon dioxide dissolves in seawater,"},{"time":77763,"text":"it undergoes a number\nof chemical reactions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":80420,"text":"Now lucky for you,"},{"time":81610,"text":"I don't have time to get into\nthe details of the chemistry for today."},{"time":85388,"text":"But I'll tell you as more\ncarbon dioxide enters the ocean,"},{"time":88737,"text":"the seawater pH goes down."},{"time":91730,"text":"And this basically means that there\nis an increase in ocean acidity."},{"time":96348,"text":"And this whole process\nis called ocean acidification."},{"time":100904,"text":"And it's happening\nalongside climate change."},{"time":104356,"text":"Scientists have been monitoring\nocean acidification for over two decades."},{"time":108998,"text":"This figure is an important\ntime series in Hawaii,"},{"time":111696,"text":"and the top line shows steadily increasing\nconcentrations of carbon dioxide,"},{"time":116616,"text":"or CO2 gas, in the atmosphere."},{"time":119242,"text":"And this is directly as a result\nof human activities."},{"time":123340,"text":"The line underneath shows the increasing\nconcentrations of carbon dioxide"},{"time":127396,"text":"that is dissolved\nin the surface of the ocean"},{"time":130578,"text":"which you can see is increasing\nat the same rate"},{"time":133562,"text":"as carbon dioxide in the atmosphere\nsince measurements began."},{"time":136927,"text":"The line on the bottom shows\nthen shows the change in chemistry."},{"time":139959,"text":"As more carbon dioxide\nhas entered the ocean,"},{"time":142810,"text":"the seawater pH has gone down,"},{"time":145551,"text":"which basically means there has been\nan increase in ocean acidity."},{"time":151185,"text":"Now in Ireland, scientists are also\nmonitoring ocean acidification --"},{"time":155280,"text":"scientists at the Marine\nInstitute and NUI Galway."},{"time":158224,"text":"And we, too, are seeing\nacidification at the same rate"},{"time":162398,"text":"as these main ocean time-series\nsites around the world."},{"time":165866,"text":"So it's happening right at our doorstep."}]},{"cues":[{"time":169570,"text":"Now I'd like to give you an example\nof just how we collect our data"},{"time":172753,"text":"to monitor a changing ocean."},{"time":175189,"text":"Firstly we collect a lot of our samples\nin the middle of winter."},{"time":178269,"text":"So as you can imagine,\nin the North Atlantic"},{"time":180433,"text":"we get hit with some seriously\nstormy conditions --"},{"time":183149,"text":"so not for any of you\nwho get a little motion sickness,"},{"time":185807,"text":"but we are collecting\nsome very valuable data."},{"time":188592,"text":"So we lower this instrument\nover the side of the ship,"},{"time":191496,"text":"and there are sensors\nthat are mounted on the bottom"},{"time":193957,"text":"that can tell us information about\nthe surrounding water,"},{"time":196655,"text":"such as temperature\nor dissolved oxygen."},{"time":199450,"text":"And then we can collect our seawater\nsamples in these large bottles."},{"time":203432,"text":"So we start at the bottom,\nwhich can be over four kilometers deep"},{"time":206709,"text":"just off our continental shelf,"},{"time":208812,"text":"and we take samples at regular intervals\nright up to the surface."},{"time":212875,"text":"We take the seawater back on the deck,"},{"time":215271,"text":"and then we can either\nanalyze them on the ship"},{"time":217675,"text":"or back in the laboratory\nfor the different chemicals parameters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":221167,"text":"But why should we care?"},{"time":222651,"text":"How is ocean acidification\ngoing to affect all of us?"},{"time":228754,"text":"Well, here are the worrying facts."},{"time":232777,"text":"There has already been an increase\nin ocean acidity of 26 percent"},{"time":238604,"text":"since pre-industrial times,\nwhich is directly due to human activities."},{"time":243651,"text":"Unless we can start slowing down\nour carbon dioxide emissions,"},{"time":248031,"text":"we're expecting an increase\nin ocean acidity of 170 percent"},{"time":254388,"text":"by the end of this century."},{"time":257713,"text":"I mean this is within\nour children's lifetime."},{"time":261505,"text":"This rate of acidification\nis 10 times faster"},{"time":267148,"text":"than any acidification in our oceans\nfor over 55 million years."},{"time":274060,"text":"So our marine life have never,\never experienced"},{"time":278456,"text":"such a fast rate of change before."},{"time":281551,"text":"So we literally could not know\nhow they're going to cope."}]},{"cues":[{"time":287035,"text":"Now there was a natural acidification\nevent millions of years ago,"},{"time":291646,"text":"which was much slower\nthan what we're seeing today."},{"time":294780,"text":"And this coincided with a mass extinction\nof many marine species."},{"time":300891,"text":"So is that what we're headed for?"},{"time":303270,"text":"Well, maybe."},{"time":305031,"text":"Studies are showing\nsome species are actually doing quite well"},{"time":308548,"text":"but many are showing a negative response."},{"time":313086,"text":"One of the big concerns is\nas ocean acidity increases,"},{"time":317427,"text":"the concentration of carbonate\nions in seawater decrease."},{"time":322490,"text":"Now these ions are basically\nthe building blocks"},{"time":325426,"text":"for many marine species\nto make their shells,"},{"time":328759,"text":"for example crabs or mussels, oysters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":333774,"text":"Another example are corals."},{"time":335932,"text":"They also need these carbonate\nions in seawater"},{"time":339138,"text":"to make their coral structure\nin order to build coral reefs."},{"time":344367,"text":"As ocean acidity increases"},{"time":346779,"text":"and the concentration\nof carbonate ions decrease,"},{"time":350462,"text":"these species first find it more difficult\nto make their shells."},{"time":355231,"text":"And at even even lower levels,\nthey can actually begin to dissolve."}]},{"cues":[{"time":360215,"text":"This here is a pteropod,\nit's called a sea butterfly."},{"time":363516,"text":"And it's an important food source\nin the ocean for many species,"},{"time":366952,"text":"from krill to salmon right up to whales."},{"time":371388,"text":"The shell of the pteropod\nwas placed into seawater"},{"time":374927,"text":"at a pH that we're expecting\nby the end of this century."},{"time":379204,"text":"After only 45 days\nat this very realistic pH,"},{"time":385040,"text":"you can see the shell\nhas almost completely dissolved."},{"time":389555,"text":"So ocean acidification could affect\nright up through the food chain --"},{"time":393824,"text":"and right onto our dinner plates."},{"time":396474,"text":"I mean who here\nlikes shellfish? Or salmon?"},{"time":400682,"text":"Or many other fish species"},{"time":402335,"text":"whose food source\nin the ocean could be affected?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":406126,"text":"These are cold-water corals."},{"time":408112,"text":"And did you know we actually have\ncold-water corals in Irish waters,"},{"time":411670,"text":"just off our continental shelf?"},{"time":414023,"text":"And they support rich biodiversity,\nincluding some very important fisheries."},{"time":418856,"text":"It's projected that\nby the end of this century,"},{"time":422226,"text":"70 percent of all known cold-water corals\nin the entire ocean"},{"time":428577,"text":"will be surrounded by seawater\nthat is dissolving their coral structure."},{"time":436850,"text":"The last example I have\nare these healthy tropical corals."},{"time":441072,"text":"They were placed in seawater at a pH\nwe're expecting by the year 2100."},{"time":447484,"text":"After six months, the coral\nhas almost completely dissolved."},{"time":454170,"text":"Now coral reefs support"},{"time":456606,"text":"25 percent of all marine life\nin the entire ocean."},{"time":463870,"text":"All marine life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":466068,"text":"So you can see: ocean\nacidification is a global threat."},{"time":471038,"text":"I have an eight-month-old baby boy."},{"time":473980,"text":"Unless we start now to slow this down,"},{"time":478003,"text":"I dread to think what our oceans\nwill look like when he's a grown man."},{"time":483700,"text":"We will see acidification."},{"time":485830,"text":"We have already put too much\ncarbon dioxide into the atmosphere."},{"time":491030,"text":"But we can slow this down."},{"time":494096,"text":"We can prevent the worst-case scenario."},{"time":498750,"text":"The only way of doing that"},{"time":501013,"text":"is by reducing our\ncarbon dioxide emissions."},{"time":505010,"text":"This is important for both you and I,\nfor industry, for governments."}]},{"cues":[{"time":509600,"text":"We need to work together,\nslow down global warming"},{"time":513500,"text":"slow down ocean acidification"},{"time":516080,"text":"and help to maintain a healthy ocean\nand a healthy planet"},{"time":520839,"text":"for our generation\nand for generations to come."}]},{"cues":[{"time":525324,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}